Job Title: Head of Technology - Data & AI Engineering - Hawthorn East
Ad Text:
We've been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with 120,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you'll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you'll also get to see your impact.

About the team

As the way Australians shop continues to evolve, our Data and AI Team keep Coles at the forefront of modern retail. We combine data, artificial intelligence, and applied engineering to reimagine how our stores, supply chain, and digital channels operate, creating smarter, more connected, and seamless experiences for our customers and team members.

Operating as a centralised development and enablement function within Coles Technology, the team unites product, engineering, and platform capabilities to deliver the intelligence layer of the enterprise. We serve every part of Coles from computer vision applications that enhance in-store experiences and reduce loss, to forecasting, optimisation, and decision-support solutions that drive efficiency, accuracy, and agility across our supply chain, retail operations, and corporate functions.

The scale and impact of this work are significant. Coles serves millions of customers each week across more than a thousand stores nationwide, and our AI and data capabilities provide the intelligence that underpins how we plan, move, sell, and serve. By combining deep data capability with applied AI and modern engineering, we’re enabling Coles to become a truly AI-enabled enterprise, transforming how we operate and how Australia shops every day.

About the role

This exciting position within our Data and AI team will be pivotal in architecting and leading the development of scalable, high-performance AI/ML and data solutions.

To be successful in this role, you will aim for the below:

Lead domain-specific squads including software engineers, data engineers, ML engineers, data scientists, and UX designers
Translate product vision into engineered outcomes, ensuring measurable business value aligned with corporate priorities.
Integrate AI and ML capabilities into operational systems and applications, embedding intelligence into the way Coles plans, moves, and serves.
Establish and champion best practices in software, data, and AI engineering — including secure, compliant, and efficient development and deployment.
Drive automation, tooling, and CI/CD practices to enable reliable, repeatable delivery of AI-powered solutions.
Ensure all AI and data solutions comply with Coles’ security, privacy, and ethical standards, meeting regulatory obligations and supporting responsible AI governance.
Collaborate closely with Product and Platform leaders to ensure seamless integration with shared data assets, infrastructure, and services.
Foster a culture of experimentation and continuous improvement, exploring emerging AI, agentic, and generative capabilities responsibly.
Make pragmatic build-versus-buy decisions, balancing innovation, cost, and speed to value.

You are a strategic engineering leader who thrives at the intersection of AI, software, and product development. You build bridges across teams — partnering with product, technology, and business leaders to embed intelligence into Coles’ operations at scale.

You combine technical credibility with the ability to inspire, influence, and align diverse stakeholders. Known for fostering engineering excellence and building trusted, high-performing teams, you balance innovation with pragmatism, people with process, and vision with delivery.

Experience required

Proven years of experience in AI/ML engineering, with a clear progression into management roles.
Proven ability to design and architect complex scalable AI/ML systems and data pipelines
Software engineering with app development background – strong programming skills
Experience with GenAI and agentic workflows
Significant experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP).
A blend of software engineering and machine learning experience.
Experience with cloud data platforms (Snowflake, DataBricks) and reporting tools (Power BI)
Experience with MLOps practices (CI/CD, model monitoring, etc.).
Evidence of building AI models and integrating them into business workflows (API management, load management, integration, data security, logging etc)
Experience in complex corporate environments, retail experience preferred.
Understanding of delivering under Agile methodology

Commercial Skills and Formal Qualifications
Proficiency in programming languages like Python, Java, or C++.
Experience with machine learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).
Knowledge of data engineering tools and technologies (Spark, Kafka, databases).
Cloud platform expertise.
Leadership and team management skills.
Good understanding of software architecture.
A Bachelor's or Master's Degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Maths, or a related field.

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.

Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.

Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hot deals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.

Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks.’ You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.

Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.

Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.

Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Job ID: 164945 

Employment Type: Full time 

#LI-MM1

Who are we?  

Humanforceʼs vision is to make work easier and life better for frontline and flexible workforces. 

Humanforce provides the market leading, best-in-one human capital management (HCM) suite for frontline and flexible workforces - without compromise. Our employee centered, intelligent and compliant HCM suite is highly integrated and composable, and consists of Workforce Management (WFM), HR, Talent, Payroll, and Wellbeing.  

Humanforce has built strong foundations since its founding in 2002. We help over 2300 customers and almost 1 million employees under management in 30+ countries, across a wide range of industries, including aged, child and health care; education; hospitality; retail; local government and more. Today, we have offices across Australia, New Zealand, United Kingdom, North America and the Philippines.

Customers choose Humanforce because we enable them to deliver an exceptional employee experience, build a compelling employee value proposition, and connect the flow of the worlds talent with the growth, productivity and efficiency objectives of frontline and flexible workforces.

Who you are

Help build and run the data infrastructure for our real-time, customer-facing analytics platform. You’ll focus on reliable and performant CDC ingestion, transformation, governance, and operational excellence so our analysts can publish high-quality analytics within our analytics platform.

Day to day, you’ll partner closely with our Senior Data Engineer to work across the breadth of our data infrastructure Streamkap, dbt Core, ClickHouse, and AWS to continually improve and extend our data platform.

You’ll collaborate with a cross-functional squad (Data Analyst, DBA, and Software Engineers). If you’re a driven, self-motivated problem solver who enjoys shaping an evolving architecture, is comfortable with ambiguous problem spaces, and takes pride in innovative yet pragmatic solutions, you’ll have clear ownership and impact on a critical, customer-visible product suite. 

What you will do

Build and maintain reliable data pipelines that ingest CDC streams (Streamkap) and batch data into ClickHouse, transforming with dbt Core.

Implement the orchestrator to schedule, monitor, and recover our pipelines.

Enhance ELT performance and stability, and troubleshoot issues across staging and production environments.

Implement and uphold data governance practices: testing, documentation, and service levels (e.g., freshness/completeness SLIs/SLOs) with lineage.

Operate and observe pipelines using AWS services

Collaborate with a cross-functional team (Senior Data Engineer, Data Analyst, DBA, Software Engineers, Product Managers) to deliver trustworthy datasets consumed in ThoughtSpot.

Ensure integrity, reliability, and security of the data engineering architecture.

Our stack

Warehouse: ClickHouse

Ingestion/CDC: Streamkap

Transformations: dbt Core

Cloud: AWS (S3, Lambda, ECS, EventBridge)

Infra/CI: Terraform, GitHub Actions

 What you’ll need

3+ years of hands-on data engineering.

Strong SQL and Python (non-negotiable).

Experience building and maintaining Cloud Data Warehouse Infrastructure (ideally ClickHouse or a background in Snowflake/BigQuery/Redshift and a willingness to learn ClickHouse).

Experience building and operating production data pipelines (e.g., with dbt Core).

Practical experience with AWS and Dockerised workloads.

Understanding of modern ELT practices, testing, and documentation.

Direct experience using AI tools in your day-to-day work, or a strong openness and eagerness to learn how to apply them to enhance outcomes.

Some ‘nice to have’

Experience with CDC+Kafka based ingestion tools (such as Streamkap) for near-real-time ingestion.

Terraform and infrastructure-as-code workflows;

CI/CD workflows with GitHub Actions.

Security-minded habits (IAM, tenancy isolation, PII handling).

Agile delivery experience (Jira) and code review via GitHub PRs.

Our values  

We are bold  

We are all in  

We are customer obsessed  

We do what we say  

We are good humans  

Our approach to flexibility

We are passionate about people making their own decisions about where and when they work. Our hybrid model of minimum two days a week of in office moments supports flexibility tailored to individual and team needs, empowering people to achieve their career and personal goals. 

Benefits

A truly flexible workplace through our Flex@HF approach 

The opportunity to be part of a fast-growing global tech company 

A focus on learning and development through Humanforce HR 

A generous talent referral program – know great people, be rewarded 

12 weeks paid parental leave for primary careers, 4 weeks for secondary 

4 extra days leave to focus on your wellbeing 

Contemporary and practical Employee Assistance Program  

A cool reward and recognition program – shout to your colleagues and earn points to spend 

Access to our own financial wellbeing platform Thrive – including earned wage access, tools to budget and save, perks and cashback across 100s of Australian retailers 

Fun, collaborative culture with passionate people 

A workplace where you can genuinely improve the world of work!  

We are a diverse and dispersed organisation and are actively looking to grow our team with individuals from all diverse backgrounds. We encourage applicants from all backgrounds, cultures, ages, genders, neurodiversity, religions, sexual orientations, and experiences to apply.

QuantX Labs, based in the vibrant Lot Fourteen innovation precinct in Adelaide, is advancing the frontier of quantum sensing, atomic clocks and satellite payload technologies. We’re a team of engineers, physicists and scientists developing world-first deep-tech solutions with applications across Defence, Space, and critical national infrastructure.

We are seeking a Firmware Engineer who will play a pivotal role in developing, integrating, and optimising firmware for next-generation products, from quantum sensing systems to orbital atomic clocks.

This role is perfect for a curious, driven engineer who thrives in multidisciplinary teams and wants to see their work literally reach orbit.

What You’ll Do

You will work across the full product lifecycle — design, prototyping, integration, and verification — helping turn research into real-world solutions.

Your responsibilities will include:

• Designing and developing firmware, embedded systems and FPGA code for innovative products.

• Integrating hardware, firmware, and software systems, including defence and satellite payload applications.

• Implementing digital signal processing (DSP) algorithms and real-time embedded control systems.

• Developing and maintaining communication protocols and embedded Linux systems.

• Supporting the design and verification of high-speed data acquisition and frequency systems.

• Contributing to project planning, documentation, and peer review processes.

• Collaborating with a diverse team of engineers, physicists, and researchers.

About You

You’re technically excellent, detail-oriented, and motivated by complex challenges. You enjoy working on multidisciplinary projects and want to see your work make an impact beyond Earth.

Essential skills & experience:

• Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, or a related field.

• 1+ years’ experience in firmware, FPGA, or embedded systems development.

• Proficiency in VHDL, C/C++, and Python.

• Experience with AMD/Xilinx toolchains (Vivado, Vitis, Vitis HLS) or MicroSemi (Libero SoC).

• Experience with DSP, real-time control, and high-speed digital systems.

• Strong understanding of embedded Linux and microprocessor/ARM integration.

Desirable experience:

• Experience developing firmware for satellite or space-based systems.

• Background in digital or hybrid feedback control systems.

• Familiarity with MATLAB/SIMULINK, machine learning for signal analysis, or mesh-networking protocols.

• Use of version control and automated validation/testing tools.

Why Join Us

• Work on technologies that are defining the future of quantum and space innovation.

• Be part of a collaborative and high-performing team that values respect, excellence, and integrity.

• Enjoy a dynamic, flexible work environment (38 hours/week between 8am–6pm).

• Access professional growth opportunities and projects at the cutting edge of science and engineering.

• Thrive within the Lot Fourteen innovation hub — Adelaide’s centre for deep-tech and defence innovation.

We’ve partnered with a leading global technology innovator that’s scaling a world-class AI engineering team here in Australia. This team is building a next-generation document-intelligence platform from the ground up, combining computer vision, NLP, and large-language-model research to solve some of the most complex problems in document automation and understanding.
This isn’t a “prompt-engineering” or fine-tuning role.

It’s true deep-tech! building foundational AI systems alongside top ML minds in the US and Australia, backed by a significant R&D budget and a clear mandate for innovation.

What You’ll Do
Design, build, and train AI models for NLP, LLMs, OCR and object detection
Develop and optimise core model architectures, nothing pre-built or off-the-shelf
Collaborate with global researchers, principal engineers, and data scientists
Contribute to a new AI platform driving document intelligence at enterprise scale
Work across the full lifecycle: experimentation → model design → deployment → evaluation
Tech Environment
Python, PyTorch, TensorFlow
YOLO / Object Detection, Transformers / LLMs
Computer-vision pipelines & custom training infrastructure
Experience with NLP, OCR, or multimodal architectures is highly regarded
What We’re Looking For
Proven experience building end-to-end ML models from scratch
Strong foundation in deep learning, NLP, or CV research
Comfortable working across uncharted, R&D-heavy environments
Hands-on, curious, and experimental—comfortable with ambiguity
Bonus: publications, open-source contributions, or PhD in a relevant field
Why Join
Greenfield architecture (no legacy systems)
Multi-million-dollar R&D investment and genuine global scale
Work directly with some of the world’s top AI researchers and engineers
Operate at the bleeding edge of applied AI
Flexible hybrid setup; Australia-based team with strong US collaboration
If you’re a proven Machine Learning Engineer who’s built real systems (not just used pre-trained ones) and you want to help define the future of applied AI, we’d love to chat.

Send a message or your CV for a confidential discussion.

Quantum-Systems is more than a workplace. We are transforming the way data is acquired and decisions are made through our AI-powered unmanned aerial systems. We play to change the game. To make our mark on the center stage.

Do you have what it takes?

Quantum-Systems Australia is seeking a Linux Software Engineer.

Don't miss this opportunity to join us as we develop our world-class capability right here in Redbank. With major contracts in process and more on the way, this role will offer amazing experience for the right candidate.

Bring your work experience and join us on this incredible journey.

About Us:

Quantum-Systems is at the forefront of autonomous, AI-powered aerial robotics globally. Our Australian subsidiary, Quantum-Systems Australia, operates in the Defence, Security, and Commercial markets, specialising in Uncrewed Aerial Vehicles (UAS) in the Asia-Pacific region.

Summary:

The role is accountable for designing and documenting system interfaces and architecture, managing build systems and release pipelines, and coordinating across teams and suppliers. It encompasses the full lifecycle of software and system support, including systematic analysis, risk assessment, testing at all levels, and fault investigation during development, production, and in-service operations.

Responsibilities:

Maintaining existing, as well as creating new Linux applications on the unmanned aircraft.
Designing and coordinating interfaces between teams, documenting the architecture and design decisions.
Integration of hardware and 3rd-party software into the Linux system, aligning with suppliers and other teams.
Testing of existing and new applications. This includes writing unit tests, integration tests, functional tests, and acceptance tests.
Analysing logs from both test flights as well as real-world customer issues.
Fault finding and issue tracking in production and maintenance.
Conduct systematic analysis and risk assessment, implementing strategies to mitigate potential obstacles and ensure success. 

Qualifications & Experience:

Required

Tertiary degree in Software Engineering, or related field, or equivalent relevant experience.
Experience in embedded software development, preferably in robotics.
Australian Citizenship and ability to hold a Security Clearance.
Strong proficiency in C/C++.
Familiarity with scripting languages: Bash & Python.
Solid understanding of Linux commands (e.g. grep, telnet, tcpdump).
Hands-on experience with debugging tools (e.g., GDB, strace, perf) and log analysis.
Experience with CI/CD pipelines, version control systems (e.g., Git), and release management.
Experience with CMAKE and an understanding of compilation.
Basic knowledge of communication protocols (UDP/TCP, MAVLink CAN Bus, Serial, Ethernet).

Desired

Familiarity with middleware and interface standards such as DDS.
Knowledge of containerisation technologies (e.g., Docker) and virtualisation.
Passion for Drones.

Why Join Us?

We offer a dynamic and agile workplace culture, one that embraces challenges and thrives on breaking new ground. Our employees are creative and innovative thinkers, communicating with clarity, conviction and enthusiasm.

We embrace diversity and inclusion in a vibrant, engaging environment. Our people are authentic, resilient, and influential, and we deliver results.

Note: A Defence security clearance is required for this role, so your nationality may be a factor in determining your suitability for this position.

What are you waiting for? We’d love you to join us and make your mark in the exciting world of Uncrewed Aerial Vehicles!

APPLY NOW!

Quantum-Systems Pty Ltd. is an equal opportunity employer committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace. We do not accept unlawful discrimination in our recruitment or employment practices and encourage applications from all suitably skilled candidates.

Applicants are encouraged to share with our recruitment team any accommodations required during the recruitment process.

About Icon Water

Icon Water is an iconic Canberra business with a history of providing essential services to Canberra for over 100 years.

We are the ACT’s supplier of essential water and wastewater services and have proudly served our community for over 100 years – sourcing, treating and supplying water, and managing Canberra’s wastewater network. Our work is essential to the health, prosperity and liveability of the region, and we are committed to environmental, social and financial sustainability in everything we do.

Icon Water is a purpose driven organisation where everyone contributes to our core business, ensuring high quality drinking water and sustainable wastewater treatment. Icon Water’s culture is driven by our values of care, connection, community and courage. These are values we see in action every day as we challenge ourselves to meet the expectations of our community.  




Be part of a high-performing, dynamic, and professional Reliability Engineering Team

Are you passionate about delivering predictive, risk-based programs of work that ensure safe and reliable water and wastewater services for our community?
Do you want to contribute to business strategy implementation by proactively managing asset risk and investment, using predictive insights to stay ahead of challenges from an ageing network, rising failure risks, performance issues, and increasing costs?
Do you have a background in reliability engineering or maintenance, strong digital and systems capability, and a passion for driving change across people, processes, and technology?

If so, we invite you to apply for the position of Reliability Engineer with Icon Water.

About this role: We are seeking a collaborative, digitally savvy, systems-strong, detail-oriented, and results-focused Reliability Engineer to drive reliability improvement initiatives across our asset base. This is a role where you will make a tangible contribution to the community, engage daily with senior leaders, peers, and colleagues, and work across both technical and operational areas to deliver real outcomes.

This role is accountable for implementing reliability improvements that support Icon Water’s asset management, reliability, and maintenance functions-directly contributing to our strategic focus areas.

You will:

Deliver reliability improvement initiatives and embed change through effective engagement and communication.
Drive integration and use of RCM/WAM systems (e.g. OnePM–WAM and OnePM Connect) to enable accelerated maintenance programme speed of change.
Implement and apply asset health and RCM tools to optimise maintenance strategies, identify critical spares, improve program effectiveness, and balance cost, risk, reliability, and performance.
Coordinate operational readiness and asset health activities (e.g. Top 10 Focus Asset Class) to optimise asset lifecycle value.
Leverage systems such as OnePM, WAM, and Asset Health tools to identify end-of-life triggers, resolve reliability issues, and ensure consistent works management.
Drive asset health data quality improvements through updating assessment outcomes in CMMS and RCM systems.

What We’re Looking For:  The Reliability Engineer role is part of the Infrastructure Reliability & Performance Branch within the Infrastructure Services Group. The Branch is committed to developing and implementing leading asset management approaches to maximise asset reliability and performance in the challenging environment of balancing aging assets and customer requirements.

Who We’re Looking For: We’re seeking a dedicated individual, enthusiastic to implement leading reliability practices at Icon Water. To be successful for this role, you will need:

Tertiary qualifications in Engineering or a related discipline (Mechanical or Civil preferred).
Experience in an industrial, manufacturing, or utility service delivery environment (desirable).
Strong systems and digital capability, including demonstrated skills in SQL (or similar), Power BI, programming, and mobility solutions; exposure to CMMS implementation or other enterprise asset management systems (essential)
Demonstrated experience in preventative and predictive maintenance strategies, reliability techniques, tools, and systems (e.g. RCM, Weibull, RCA, FMECA, Asset Health, Reliability Block Diagrams) with the ability to develop and implement industry best practices.
Proven experience in assessing asset health, performance, and condition of equipment common to utilities or similar environments.
Knowledge and/or experience in condition monitoring techniques such as vibration analysis, thermography, oil analysis, and alignment.
Experience working with water supply and wastewater treatment assets (desirable).
Working knowledge of ISO 55001 requirements.
Demonstrated ability to solve complex problems, influence and lead change, and work collaboratively across functions within a commercial environment.
Strong communication and negotiation skills, with the ability to influence peers and workgroups in complex environments.
Demonstrated experience in applying cost-effective risk management and predictive techniques to critically analyse solution options.
Commitment to continuous improvement, including preparation of management system documentation.
Familiarity with CMMS (Oracle will be highly regarded), reliability engineering software, and integrity assurance systems.

To find out more about the role you can view the detailed Position Description on our Careers Portal.

or  contact Rae Kyaw Kyaw, Lead Reliability Improvement Engineer on 0404 091 201 or ye.kyawkyaw@iconwater.com.au learn more about this opportunity.

If you’re ready to make a real impact and be part of a company that values your expertise, apply now.

Job description:

Australian Unity is embarking on a major transformation, shifting from traditional automation toward an intelligent, AI-powered future. We're looking for a Senior AI Automation Engineer to help shape this next generation of automation: one where AI Agents, large language models (LLMs), and modern frameworks transform how we work and deliver value to our customers.

In this hands on and strategic role, you'll play a key part in modernising our automation ecosystem; maintaining and enhancing current platforms (Appian, UiPath, Power Automate) while designing and implementing cutting-edge, AI-driven automation ecosystem. You'll combine deep technical expertise with creative problem solving, using first principles thinking to challenge the status quo, simplify complexity, and drive enterprise wide efficiency.

This is a unique opportunity to lead the transition from classical RPA to AI-centric automation, setting the foundation for an adaptive, scalable, and future-ready technology landscape.

What You'll Do

Lead end-to-end automation delivery, from concept to deployment.

Modernise existing Automation ecosystem while building the foundations for AI Agent driven automation.

Design and implement next generation automation using Generative AI, MCP Servers, and agent frameworks, extending the boundaries of what automation can do.

Define and embed best practice design patterns, reusable modules, and delivery frameworks that improve speed, scalability, and governance.

Monitor and optimise automation performance and outcomes to ensure business impact and alignment with strategic goals.

Maintain and enhance current automation pipelines (Appian, UiPath, Power Automate), ensuring stability as we evolve the stack.

Collaborate across business and technology teams to translate complex problems into practical, measurable automation solutions.

Mentor and guide junior and offshore engineers, fostering a culture of innovation and technical excellence.

Stay ahead of emerging technologies in AI, automation, and machine learning and bring fresh ideas that keep us at the forefront of innovation.

About You

We are looking for an innovator who's curious, forward-thinking, and thrives on solving complex challenges. You will bring a mix of hands-on technical skill and architectural vision. You question legacy approaches, design from first principles, and are excited by the possibilities of AI and automation convergence.

We also value an entrepreneur's mindset — someone who can wear multiple hats, adapt fluidly to new challenges, and take on roles beyond coding to deliver meaningful business impact.
Start-up or similar experience that demonstrates versatility, ownership, and comfort operating in a fast-changing environment — whether as a founder or an early employee — will be highly regarded.

You will have:

Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.

5 years+ commercial experience in relevant technical role.

You'll have experience with:

Generative AI & agentic frameworks (LangChain, LangGraph, AutoGen, MCP Servers, etc.)

Proficiency in at least one programming language (preferably Python), with strong OOP and design-pattern skills, and the ability to deliver high-quality, well-tested code.

The ability to collaborate with stakeholders and communicate technical concepts clearly

Technology/AI architecture, governance, and scalability in enterprise environments

Familiarity with RPA/BPA platforms such as UiPath, Appian, and Power Automate or strong willingness to learn.

 What's on Offer:

You will enjoy a range of great employee benefits and rewards including:

Competitive salary + bonus program

Enjoy additional yearly Well-Being and Community leave days

14-week paid parental leave, with equal benefit for both parents

Employee Referral Program

Employee Assistance Program - support and assistance for you and your partner at those times in life when you need it most

Maxxia Rewards - a great range of discounts and benefits at selected retail outlets, department stores, attractions, travel, cinemas, restaurants.

Discounts across the Australian Unity business including Private Health Insurance, General Insurance + more!

Available access to LinkedIn Learning courses through our great Learning platform

For further benefits visit: https://www.australianunity.com.au/careers/culture

 Australian Unity is an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from all members of the community, including people of Aboriginal and Torres strait Islander descent, culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and, mature aged people.

Job Title: Senior Data Scientist - Sydney - Gain Gen AI up to $170,000 plus super
Ad Text:
Senior Data Scientist - Sydney up to $170,000 plus super - Gain Gen AI - Commercial and out comes focused

We’re seeking a hands-on Data Scientist who can turn complex data into actionable insights and measurable business outcomes. You’ve built and productionised models, worked across predictive analytics and GenAI, and thrive on creating commercial impact from day one. This role suits someone who enjoys solving real-world problems, engaging with stakeholders, and using data science to shape decisions and improve customer experiences.

The Opportunity

You’ll join a major Australian organisation with a growing analytics function and rich datasets, this is a chance to influence data strategy, work on high-impact initiatives, and contribute to a data-driven culture.
You’ll collaborate with technical and business teams, applying expertise in predictive modelling, LLMs, and GenAI to deliver tangible value across multiple areas of the business.

Key Responsibilities
Develop, productionise, and optimise data science models that drive business outcomes.
Translate complex data into insights that inform strategic decisions.
Work collaboratively across teams to embed data-driven decision-making.
Stay hands-on with Python, SQL, and modern ML/AI frameworks.
Promote a proactive, commercially focused approach to analytics.
About You
Proven experience delivering commercial impact through data science.
Strong technical skills in Python, SQL, predictive modelling, LLMs, and GenAI.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement abilities.
Curious, outcome-driven, and able to work autonomously in a fast-paced environment.
Why Apply?
Strategic, hands-on role with real commercial influence.
Gain Gen AI.
Autonomous role - add value from day one.

Lab3 is one of the largest Azure engineering practices in the Australasia region with a focus on Cloud & DevOps, Data, IoT & AI, Modern Workplace, Modern Apps & Integration, Security, and Network services.

We are on the hunt for a Senior Engineer (Professional Services) with experience across Microsoft modern workplace management (e.g. M365, Intune, Application Packaging & Windows SOE).

This will be a 6-12 month contract with likelihood of extension. NV1 AGSVA security clearance is essential for this engagement.


The role:

You will lead technical client engagements, drive high level design, consult, undertake maturity assessments and delivery for our Modern Workplace practice. These will address clients’ requirements of scalability, reliability, security, operations and performance.  
The role will utilise technology skills in the Modern Workplace Environment, primarily in a cloud environment but with migration and on-prem skills being useful, along with strong consulting skills.
Deliver professional services that leverage solutions in the Modern Workplace space that include including AVD, Intune, App Packaging, Purview, Teams & DSC and as much of the M365 suite as possible.
Provide consulting services across a range of facets including SOE, Modern Management and end to end IT governance/security reviews.
Evaluate emerging Modern Workplace technology, develop and evolve go-to-market professional services offerings to ensure customers capitalise on the latest technology in this space.
Develop Infrastructure as Code solutions for Azure Virtual Desktop engagements.
Develop Configuration as Code libraries surrounding M365 tenant standardisation – including Intune, SOE and standardised configuration of various aspects of M365 deployment.
Work with the Solution Architecture team to develop new products and services that leverage the latest Microsoft 365 services and dependencies, as well as providing technical governance and sign-off of projects and proposals.
Present to senior business & technology leaders, conduct workshops and review architecture. Assist the presales team by providing them expertise in this field.

The right candidate:

Will have a deep and wide understanding of Modern Workplace tech (i.e. Microsoft Intune, AVD, Application Packaging, Windows SOE, Purview, Teams & DSC).
Strong consulting acumen and the ability to design & present the optimum business solutions to stakeholders
Experience running workshops with key stakeholders, the ability to talk to technical and business heads with equal ease
Experience with delivery management
Certifications in Microsoft 365/MS 500 / MS101/ MS 365 Mobility/ AZ 900 preferred
AGSVA security cleared, minimum NV1
Based anywhere in Australia

Macquarie University is hiring for a Lead Data Engineer for our Data Solutions team within Business Intelligence and Reporting. As a Lead Data Engineer, you will work with the relevant teams to lead the development and optimisation of data and analytics architecture, as well as optimising data flow and collection to deliver integrated and quality business information and reporting solutions.

Business Intelligence and Reporting is responsible for enabling evidence-based decision-making across the University.

Key Accountabilities

Adopt and enhance existing processes to design and implement data orchestration workflows, managing curated datasets through landing zones, enterprise data warehouses, and presentation layers for insight generation.

Collaborate with the lead modeller to translate requirements into production-ready outputs.

Partner with stakeholders to understand and support their data infrastructure needs, troubleshooting and resolving technical issues.

Deploy data models into production using CI/CD pipelines, ensuring seamless integration.

Develop and manage data acquisition pipelines, ingestion workflows, and data lake capabilities.

Work alongside relevant teams to deploy Machine Learning models for predictive analytics and advanced insights.

Leverage generative AI and Natural Language Processing (NLP) to implement end-to-end solutions, enabling stakeholders to derive deep insights from structured data collaborating with the Mcquarie AI Team.

Identify, design, and implement process improvements to automate workflows, optimise data delivery, and enhance infrastructure efficiency and scalability.

Create and maintain core documentation for data models, including DDLs, ETL mappings, data dictionaries, and change registers.

Support the implementation of data asset standards and governance processes to ensure data quality and compliance.

About You

Tertiary qualifications in Data Analytics, Data Science, Business, Statistics, or equivalent experience.

Proficient with database, data pipeline, and workflow management tools such as Snowflake, JIRA, Wiki, DBT, Apache Airflow, Python, Linux, and GitHub.

Advanced skills in designing, testing, and validating data transformation and ETL routines using tools like DBT, Apache Airflow, Python, and Alteryx.

Strong hands-on experience with Data Vault 2 and dimensional data model implementation.

Proven track record of providing technical leadership in the delivery of complex enterprise data or integration solutions.

Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to engage with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Experience working in an agile squad environment is desirable.
